network.param.modules.attachments

Class AttachmentManagerUpload

  • java.lang.Object
    • network.param.AbstModuleManager
      • network.param.modules.attachments.AttachmentManagerUpload
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IAttachmentManager

    public class AttachmentManagerUpload
extends AbstModuleManager
implements IAttachmentManager
    Implementation for perform upload file into ParamNetwork.

    This class in an official implementation for uploading attachments for any documents like photo's, PDF, XLS, etc.., IAttachment. Want to perform any file upload need to implement this interface IAttachment interface.

    AttachmentManagerUpload defines below categories of operations:

    • Based on the config uploadAttachments will read the file content, if any error while reading this file it will return null, otherwise it will return bytebuffer. addBulkUpload or updateBulkUpload will call while converting XLS into Param internal JSONLD format.

    • Based on the config encryptAttachment will return the file size in bytes. This method will be invoked at the time of addBulkUpload or updateBulkUpload for keep track of original size and after reading data from getFileContent(). If both values are different it will throw exception.

    • Based on the config downloadAttachment will return file last modified date in bytes. This method will be invoked at the time of addBulkUpload or updateBulkUpload for informational purpose getFileContent().

    • Based on the config encryptAndUploadAttachment will return file extension. addBulkUpload or updateBulkUpload for informational purpose getFileContent().

    • Based on the config downloadAndDecryptAttachment will return file extension. addBulkUpload or updateBulkUpload for informational purpose getFileContent().

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Jitendra Kumar Balla, ParamNetwork
